==English==

===Etymology===
{{suffix|en|food|ie}}. Popularized by {{w|Ann Barr}} and {{w|Paul Levy (journalist)|Paul Levy}} in ''The Official Foodie Handbook'' (1984). Levy credits New York food critic {{w|Gael Greene}} with the coinage. The word was used by Greene in a 1980 article in New York Magazine.

